15 SECTION 2.
16 Said chapter is further amended by adding a new Code section to read as follows:
17 "34-4-3.2.
18 (a) As used in this Code section, the term:
19 (1) 'Eligible full-time state employee' means a full-time state employee who is paid on
20 an hourly basis for actual hours worked.
21 (2) 'Full-time state employee' means an individual who works at least 30 hours per week,
22 whose employment is intended to be continuing in nature, and who receives his or her
23 compensation in a direct payment from a state agency.
24 (3) 'State agency' means any department, agency, commission, or any other institution
25 of the executive, judicial, or legislative branches of the government of this state. Such
26 term shall not include the Board of Regents of the University System of Georgia.
27 (b) Beginning January 1, 2026, all eligible full-time state employees shall be paid a
28 minimum wage of not less than $15.00 per hour."
29 SECTION 3.
30 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
